Let's try it again:

00:58:36.267 --> 00:58:38.911
no abstentions right.
You can't abstain in an

00:58:38.911 --> 00:58:41.226
interview.
So you're on the spot,

00:58:41.226 --> 00:58:44.876
you're in the boardroom,
how many think you should rent

00:58:44.876 --> 00:58:46.680
the new machine?
Raise your hands.

00:58:46.680 --> 00:58:49.486
Wave them in the air.
How many people think you

00:58:49.486 --> 00:58:53.008
should not rent the new machine?
So we're split kind of down the

00:58:53.008 --> 00:58:56.129
middle, I'm looking at my MBA
students to see which they

00:58:56.129 --> 00:58:57.971
voted.
Which did you guys vote,

00:58:57.971 --> 00:59:00.809
rent or not rent?
Rent, the MBA's seem to think

00:59:00.809 --> 00:59:02.429
rent.
We'll see if that's right.

00:59:02.429 --> 00:59:05.909
So let's move forward,
so accountant's answer.

00:59:05.909 --> 00:59:08.503
So I think what the
accountant's going to say is

00:59:08.503 --> 00:59:11.273
this.
They're going to say,

00:59:11.273 --> 00:59:16.949
right now you're producing a
million tons a year.

00:59:16.949 --> 00:59:22.280
The new machine saves you--so,
let's put per annum--let's try

00:59:22.280 --> 00:59:26.190
and be fancy--so a million tons
per annum.

00:59:26.190 --> 00:59:33.750
The new machine saves you $.50
per ton.

00:59:33.750 --> 00:59:37.497
So if you rent this new
machine, you're producing a

00:59:37.497 --> 00:59:41.170
million tons a year,
it's going to save you $.50 a

00:59:41.170 --> 00:59:46.411
ton.
So it's going to save you half

00:59:46.411 --> 00:59:52.599
of one million a year in
variable cost.

00:59:52.599 --> 00:59:56.218
Those people who were in 115 or
150 will know what I mean by

00:59:56.218 --> 00:59:58.837
variable cost.
It's the cost you're going to

00:59:58.837 --> 01:00:01.659
save in the actual production of
your fertilizer.

01:00:01.659 --> 01:00:05.219
So it saves you half a million
a year.

01:00:05.219 --> 01:00:13.500
Unfortunately,
it costs you the cost of the

01:00:13.500 --> 01:00:24.539
machine, which is a fixed cost
of $0.7 million a year.

01:00:24.539 --> 01:00:29.370
And .7 is bigger than .5,
